      "writtenOn": "2020-07-31T03:13:00Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "not sure I like this, but i might be imagining a different use than you do.\n\nAFAIU the intent is to have user code like:\n\n    // every process registers all kinds of tasks\n    cls1 :\u003d TaskClass{..} // no Handler\n    ref1 :\u003d tq.RegisterTaskClass(cls1)\n    cls2 :\u003d TaskClass{..} // no Handler\n    ref2 :\u003d tq.RegisterTaskClass(cls2)\n\n    if taskHandlingProcess {\n      handler1 :\u003d ...\n      ref1.AttachHandler(handler1)\n    }\n\n\nRight?\nIf so, why can\u0027t the handling process code look like:\n\n    if taskHandlingProcess {\n      ref1.AttachHandler(cls1, handler1)\n    }\n\n\nUPDATE: Oh, i see. The advantage of your approach is that it\u0027ll be attached to exactly the same Dispatcher with exactly the same `cls`. Can you confirm?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 213,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 224,
        "endChar": 1
      },
      "revId": "826d4ed60e87a195db8a7e0c9f18805266feade8",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
