      "writtenOn": "2020-07-31T03:20:50Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yes. I need the handler to be associate with a concrete (ID, Prototype) pair. The simplest way to do it is to associate it with already registered TaskClass. I considered tq.RegisterHandler(\u0026ProtoMessage{}), but this requires ID to be registered separate as well. Using using TaskClassRef.AttachHandler enforces this.",
